Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC has now announced the new record of 595 cases of COVID-19 today, Monday. Lagos, the epicentre of the virus’ spread, has the highest record for the day with 156 new cases.  Other states are listed below: Oyo-141 FCT-99 Edo-47 Kaduna-27 Ondo-22 Rivers-20 Osun-17 Imo-13 Plateau-10 Nasarawa-8 Anambra-8 Kano-5 Benue-5 Borno-5 Ogun-4 Taraba-3 Gombe-3 Kebbi-1 Cross Rivers-1 595 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-156Oyo-141FCT-99Edo-47Kaduna-27Ondo-22Rivers-20Osun-17Imo-13Plateau-10Nasarawa-8Anambra-8Kano-5Benue-5Borno-5Ogun-4Taraba-3Gombe-3Kebbi-1Cross Rivers-1 33,153 confirmed13,671 discharged744 deaths pic.twitter.com/juncgT4pL9 — NCDC (@NCDCgov) July 13, 2020  In total, 33,153 cases have been confirmed with COVID-19 while 13,671 have been discharged but 744 people  died.